INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','That man is best educated who knows the greatest number of things that are so, and who can do the greatest number of things to help and heal the world.','Education,Teaching','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Education is preeminently a matter of quality, not amount','Education,Teaching','Ford News',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Any man can learn anything he will, but no man can teach except to those who want to learn.','Education,Teaching','Ford News',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The short successes that can be gained in a brief time and without difficulty, are not worth much.','Technology,Advancement,Success','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Nothing can be made except by makers, nothing can be managed except by managers. Money cannot make anything and money cannot manage anything.','Business/Monopoly/Trusts','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','We are entering an era when we shall create resources which shall be so constantly renewed that the only loss will be not to use them. There will be such a plenteous supply of heat, light and power, that it will be a sin not to use all we want. This era is coming now. And it is coming by way of Water','Natural Resources/Water/Technology','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Two classes of people lose money; those who are too weak to guard what they have; those who win money by trick. They both lose in the end.','Investment,Money,Knowledge of finances','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','When people are stung in false investment schemes there are three causes; greed of something for nothing; sheer inability to know their mind; or infantile trustfulness.','Investment,Money,Knowledge of finances','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','What right have you, save service to the world, to think that other mens labor should contribute to your gains?','Investment,Money,Knowledge of finances','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The remains of the old must be decently laid away; the path of the new prepared. That is the difference between Revolution and Progress.','Progress','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Most people think that faith means believing something; oftener it means trying something, giving it a chance to prove itself','Tradition/Faith/Ethics,Practicing old ideas','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','It is regrettable that people think about our monetary system, and of our economic structure, only in times of depression.','Economics,Money,Politics','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The only prosperity the people can afford to be satisfied with is the kind that lasts','Economics,Money,Politics','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The gifted man bears his gifts into the world, not for his own benefit, but for the people among whom he is placed; for the gifts are not his, he himself is a gift to the community.','Gifted People,Obligation of Talents,Service to Others','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','People are never so likely to be wrong as when they are organized. And they never have so little freedom. Perhaps that is why the people at large keep their freedom. People can be manipulated only when they are organized.','Organizations,Unions','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The most closely organized groups and movements in the world are those which have been the least friendly to the peoples progress and liberty.','Organizations,Unions','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','With all the wealth of the world at hand, there are human beings who hunger, whole nations who suffer cold. The judgment for this condition, for misusing Natures gifts, is the judgment upon mans failure, mans unsteadiness. Leadership is the thing.','Leadership','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Profits made out of the distress of the people are always much smaller than profits made out of the most lavish service of the people at the lowest prices that competent management can make possible','Business,Profit','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Our modern industrialism, changed to motives of public service, will provide means to remove every injustice that gives soil for prejudice','Race,Injustice','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Many people are busy trying to find better ways of doing things that should not have to be done at all. There is no progress in merely finding a better way to do a useless thing.','Problem-Solving','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Politics in the true sense, have to do with the prosperity, peace and security of the people.','Politics','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','If a young man wants to fit himself for the Politics of tomorrow, let him fit himself into essential industry for the purpose of learning how best to conduct it for the whole public good.','Politics','Ford News',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Be ready to revise any system, scrap any method, abandon any theory, if the success of the job requires it.','Pride','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','We are here for experience, and experience is a preparation to know the Truth when we meet it.','Truth & Character,Experience','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Competition whose motive is merely to compete, to drive some other fellow out, never carries very far.','Business,Competition','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The competitor to be feared is one who never bothers about you at all but goes on making his own business better all the time.','Business,Competition','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Businesses that grow by development and improvement do not die.','Business,Competition','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','There is no failure except failure to serve ones purpose.','Government,Progressive Government','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Thinking calls for facts; facts are found by digging; but he who has gathered this wealth is well equipped for life.','Education,Ideas;','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Experience is the harvest of life, and every harvest is the result of a sowing. The experience which young people must crave is that of success in some service for which they are naturally fitted.','Education,Experience,Learning','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','There is safety in small beginnings and there is unlimited capital in the experience gained by growing.','Business,Progress','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Progress is a new season and the rule of progress is everything in its season.','Progress,Change','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','We live in an era of tremendous facts. And the facts are facts. They are also unpleasant facts, which does not decrease their factual percentage one bit. Our job is to understand them, to recognize their presence, to learn if we can what they signify and not to fall into the error of minimizing facts because they have a bitter flavor.','Truth','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Of all the follies the elder generation falls victim to this is the most foolish, namely, the constant criticism of the younger element who will not be and cannot be like ourselves because we and they are different tribes produced of different elements in the great spirit of Time.','Youth,Time,Change,Children','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','..The philosophy of life indicates that our principal business on this planet is the gaining of experience.','Living/Life,Philosophy,Truth','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','If the people really set their minds on anything it is impossible to prevent their getting what they want.','Politics,Change','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','..Yet if today has no meaning, the past was a Blank and the future is a Chaos.','History,Past,Today,Present','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Work mixed with management becomes not only easier but more profitable. The time is past when anyone can boast about hard work without having a corresponding result to show for it.','Work,Labor','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Christmas stands for the human factor which makes life tolerable midst the hurry of commerce and production. All of us need the annealing effect of Christs example to relieve the hardening we get in the daily struggle for material success.','Life,Religion,Christmas','Ford News',1923);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The world is held together by the mass of honest folk who do their daily tasks, tend their own spot in the world, and have faith that at last the Right will come fully into its own.','Honesty,Morality','Ford News',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','I do not believe that material accumulation is the whole of success, and on the other hand I do not believe that true success ever excludes a sufficient possession of wealth-but wealth as a means, not as an end.','Success,Wealth,Self-sufficiency,Work','What is Success?',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','One needs to be successful in the conventional way to learn just how far away from success it may be.','Success,Wealth,Self-sufficiency,Work','What is Success?',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','I will build a motor car for the great multitude...constructed of the best materials, by the best men to be hired, after the simplest designs that modern engineering can devise...so low in price that no man making a good salary will be unable to own one-and enjoy with his family the blessing of hours of pleasure in Gods great open spaces.','Multitude,Automobile;','Burlingame, Henry Ford, p. 62. ',1913);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Youth should not be slandered. Boy nature and girl nature are less repressed and therefore more wholesome today than before. If they at times seem unimpressed by their elders, it is probably because we make a matter of authority what should be a matter of conference. These young people are new people sent to this scene by Destiny to take our places. They come with new visions to fulfill, new powers to exploit.','Youth,Future,Change,Learning,Children','Ford News',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','An imitation may be quite successful in its own way, but imitation can never be Success. Success is a first-hand creation.','Originality,Success,Innovation','Ford News',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The most dangerous notion a young man can acquire is that there is no more room for originality. There is no large room for anything else.','Originality,Success,Innovation','Ford News',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Little difficulties are made to swell until they fill our horizon while the real big blessings of life are dwindled down to nothing.','Troubles,Difficulties','Ford News',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Nations are great as they are prosperous as they are industrious as they are just.','Americanization,America, Nationalism','Ford News',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','There is nothing ever wrong with ability, ambition, achievement; but they can easily be wronged by being used to bad ends.','Human Nature,Success,Achievement','Ford News',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','To be good is not enough; a man must be good for something','Human Nature,Success,Achievement','Ford News',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The sense of injustice, more than the unjust condition itself, is what wears on mens minds.','Justice,Money','Ford News',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The partnership of mind and matter is one which has existed since the beginning of time and cannot be dissolved.','Intelligence,Brain and Brawn','Ford News',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The only true test of values, either of men or of things, is that of their ability to make the world a better place in which to live.','Values,Morals,Success','Ford News',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The satisfaction that arises from honest accomplishment is of far more value in the promotion of human happiness than the thrill that comes with the realization of materialistic aspirations.','Values,Morals,Success','Ford News',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','As members of the Ford Motor organization we are engaged in the production of an article of use for the people of all countries. Our principle is to make our work as profitable for the buyer as for the seller.','Inflation,Christmas,New Years','Ford News',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Much depends on people knowing what opportunity means; it doesnt mean a silver platter, it oftener means a spade. Self-help means something sterner than help yourself--reach over and take it.','Opportunity,Success,Self-Sufficiency','Ford News',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The genius of the American people is Self-Reliance.','Self-Sufficiency,Opportunity,Success','Ford News',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The difference between a good govt. system and its poor administration is easily explained; the chief administrators are not Bosses in the best sense.','Government,Politics','Ford News',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','A happy & contented nation is an example to the whole world. Where there is contentment there must be peace.','Ambition,Happiness,Success','Ford News',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','We are always seeking for those things which are in the clouds, not for those that lie at our feet.','Natural Resources,America','Ford News',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Whatever it is, people who have more spare time than people ever had before get the sense of whirlwind pressure,& repeat the common criticism that we are going too fast. Yet the people live longer than ever before, live with less effort, live on a higher plane. Is it possible that this common saying about our rapid pace is just another thoughtless mob suggestion?','Society,Leisure','Ford News',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','To resent efficiency is a mark of inefficiency.','Efficiency','Ford News',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','People who are capable of and fit for freedom liberate themselves from physical thralldom by substituting mind for muscle.','Machines,Slavery,Industrialism','Ford News',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Man minus the Machine is a slave; Man plus the Machine is a freeman.','Machines,Slavery,Industrialism','Ford News',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Every success is the mother of countless others.','Business,Opportunity,Independence,Self-Sufficiency','Ford News',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Whatever your goal in life, the beginning is knowledge and experience- or, briefly work.','Business,Employment,Knowledge','Ford News',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Getting permanent value out of a job means purpose and fitting means to ends.','Business,Education','Ford News',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Man is a comparative being. Substandard things must go before super-standard things can come.','Standardization,Progress;','Ford News',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','All life is experience, and one level is exchanged for another only when its lesson is learned.','Experience,Learning,Knowledge','Ford News',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','War is not a matter for the professional pacifist or militarist. It is for the unprofessional people. They finance and fight it, they bear its losses. Therefore, they should have the deciding voice concerning it. To do this, they require all the information upon which decisions are made. They should know in a difference, whether it is soluble by rational intelligence, or inevitable by force. Not once in a thousand instances would our people (this may not be true of all peoples, however) approve an offensive war. Never would they be lax in defensive action. For this is their country. However, most of their enemies are within it.','War','Ford News',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Hard knocks have a place and value, but hard thinking goes farther in less time.','Knowledge,Wisdom;','Ford News',1926);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','As betting at the race ring adds neither strength nor speed to the horse, so the exchange of shares in the stock market adds no capital to business, no increase in the production and no purchasing power to the market.','Finance','Ford News',1926);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','A peaceful nation is one that has the means to make war and restrains.','War & Peace,America,History,Foreign Affairs','Ford News',1926);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','But to do for the world more than the world does for you--that is Success.','Success,Opportunity','Ford News',1926);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The industrial value of leisure as a promoter of the consumption of goods,& thus as a stimulant to business have been proved.','Economics,Leisure,consumerism','Ford News',1926);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Suppression of progress plays into the hands of the social enemy. Every advance in social justice establishes the nation.','Progress,Social Justice,Politics','Ford News',1926);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Even now the business is so brisk that we are up against the proposition of keeping the factory going on one model while we tool up for another. I am glad of this because it will not necessitate a total shutdown. Only a comparatively few men will be out at a time while their departments are being tooled up for the new product. At one time it looked as if 70,000 men might be laid off temporarily but we have now scaled that down to less than 25,000 at a time. The lay-off will be brief because we need the men & we have no time to waste. At present I can only say this about the new model--it has speed, style, flexibility, & control in traffic. There is nothing quite like it in quality & price. The new car will cost more to manufacture but it will be more economical to operate.','Model A','Ford News',1927);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The Model T blazed the way for the motor industry & started the movement for good roads everywhere. It is still the pioneer car in many parts of the world which are just beginning to be motorized.','Model T','Ford News',1927);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','For a long time now, I have believed that industry & agriculture are natural partners & that they should begin to recognize & practice their partnership. Each of them is suffering from ailments which the other can cure. Agriculture needs a wider &steadier market; industrial workers need more steadier jobs. Can each be made to supply what the other needs? I think so. The link between is Chemistry. In the vicinity of Dearborn we are farming twenty thousand acres for everything from sunflowers to soy beans. We pass the crops through our laboratory to learn how they may be used in the manufacture of motor cars &, thus provide an industrial market for the farmers products.','Industry/Agriculture,Dearborn,Farming','Ford News',1933);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Henry Ford in a statement said: No one loses anything by raising wages as soon as he is able. It has always paid us. Low wages are the most costly any employer can pay. It is like using low-grade material--the waste makes it very expensive in the end. There is no economy in cheap labor or cheap material. The hardest thing I ever had to do was to reduce wages. I think we were the last big company to come to it. Now I am mighty glad that wages are climbing again.','Labor,Wages,Ford Motor Co','Ford News',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The depression was just a state of mind. It is over for everyone who has changed his state of mind.','Depression,Automobile industry,Ford Motor Co','Ford News',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Individualism is what makes cooperation worth living.','Miscellaneous,American Spirit,Industry;','Ford News',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Many people seem to believe that Greenfield Village & the Edison Institute & Museum at Dearborn, with their specimens of earlier type of American life & industry, are just a kind of antiquarian hobby of mine. I do not deny that they have given me a great deal of interest & pleasure. But the project is vastly more than a hobby. It has very definite purposes, & I hope will have results lasting down the years. One purpose is to remind the public who visit it & sometimes there are thousands a day--of how far& how fast we have come in technical progress in the last century or so. If we have come so far & so fast, is it likely that we shall stop now?','HFM&GV,Progress,Edison Institute','Ford News',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','We wish all users of Ford cars to know what they are entitled to.','Customer Service,Ford Motor Co;','Ford News',1935);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','See what a 25-cent raise will do to us, said Mr. Ford. So they figured the daily & monthly cost of a 25-cent increase. Put on another quarter & see what that will cost, he said. And so they went on,25 cents a step...Finally the wage of $2.34 stood at $4.75--more than 100 percent increase. One of the associates--a good financial head--remarked rather sarcastically that if they were going to be fools, why not be first-class fools & make it $5...All right, said Mr. Ford, lets make it $5.','$5 Day,Wages','Ford News',1935);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','I foresee the time when industry shall no longer denude the forests which require generations to mature, nor use up the mines which were ages in making, but shall draw its raw material largely from the annual produce of the fields. I am convinced that we shall be able to get out of yearly crops most of the basic materials which we now get from forest and mine.','Industry & Agriculture,Farming','Ford News',1935);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','What I greatly hope for these children everywhere, is a new attitude toward life--free from the gullibility which thinks we can get something for nothing; free from the greed which thinks any permanent good can come of overreaching others; and, above all, expectant of change, so that when life gives them a jolt they will be fully prepared to push on eagerly along new lines.','Education,Greenfield Village,Teaching,Progress','Ford News',1936);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Fairs and public displays, Henry Ford has said, are the best means we have yet found of showing large numbers of people the real methods of industry.','Industry,Public Display','Ford News',1937);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','No unemployment insurance can be compared to an alliance between a man and a plot of land. With one foot in the land, human society is firmly balanced against most economic uncertainties. With a job to supply him with cash, and a plot of land to guarantee him support, the individual is doubly secure. Stocks may fail, but seedtime and harvest do not fail.','Industry & Agriculture,Self-Sufficiency,Economics','Ford News',1937);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','An educated person, I think, is one who not only knows a lot, but knows how to do a lot of things.','Education,Experience,Religion','Ford News',1937);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','We have had just one main purpose during these years, and that is to give the people transportation of the most dependable quality at the lowest possible cost. Our car was called the Universal Car thirty years ago, because it fulfilled so many needs; it is The Universal Car today for the same reason.','Customer Service,Model T,Ford Motor Co,Transportation','Ford News',1938);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','History is more or less bunk.','History is Bunk','Chicago Tribune',1916);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','I dont know anybody so old he cant do something useful. Just give them a chance and see.','Age,Hard Work','Hartford Courant, Fred C. Kelly',1935);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','America is not a land of money but of wealth-not a land of rich people, but of successful workers.','America,Success,Wealth','Forbes Magazine',1943);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The basically simple things are best, whether its automobiles or diets or philosophy.','Automobiles,Simplicity','N.Y World-Telegram',1943);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The young people got me interested in aviation. It is part of the motor age. Development is dependent on power.','Aviation,Youth','N.Y American',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','What America needs most is aviation.','Aviation,America','Florida Times Union',1929);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','I can visualize the time when almost every family will have a small plane in their back yard.','Aviation,American Life','Detroit Times',1941);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','When bankers get into business they usually destroy it.','Banks and Bankers,Business,the Depression','N.Y Times',1933);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Whenever you get the idea that you are fixed or that anything is fixed for life, youd better get ready for a sudden change.','Change,Life','N.Y World-Telegram',1933);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The Bible does not need advertising by me, but I wish more people could be persuaded to read it. Perhaps if they had been, we should not have this war on our hands. For greed and idleness brought it on.','Bible, Idleness, Greed, World War II','N.Y Times Magazine',1943);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Greatest thing we can produce is character. Everything else can be taken from us, but not our character.','Character','Cincinnati Times Star',1937);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Look beyond the individual to the cause of his misery.','Charity and Welfare,Philanthropy','Cosmopolitan Magazine',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','If we had more justice there would be less need of charity.','Charity and Welfare,Justice','New Orleans Times Picayune',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The only thing you can give a man without hurting him is an opportunity.','Charity and Welfare,Opportunity','New Orleans Times Picayune',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Youve got to teach youngsters the difference between right and wrong, but you shouldnt try to poke it down their throats. Let them ask the questions and then give them the answers.','Children,Youth','Think magazine',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Children have helped me a lot.','Children,Youth','True Story',1935);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Trouble with the world today is people dont go to children enough. I dont like old people. I stay away from them.','Children,Adults,Youth','Detroit Times',1938);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','There should be rivalry between men and between business.','Competition','American Magazine',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Competition is the lifeblood of industry.','Competition,Industry','Detroit News',1941);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','As far as competition is concerned, that must continue. But we must learn what competition really is. It is a striving to attain the best. To throttle it would mean to stop all progress. Certain men do not need to compete. They are pioneers.','Competition','Rotarian',1936);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Id like to devote about three years to the elimination of the cow. Theres not reason in the world why the chemist cant discover the cows secret of converting vegetation into dairy products. And theres less reason why the chemist cant do a better job of it after he learns how.','Cows,Science,Farming,Livestock','Detroit Free Press',1936);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The present method of producing milk is too laborious. I believe that we can make milk by scientific process, eliminating the cow.','Cows,Science,Farming,Livestock','N.Y American',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','..we do not hire a mans history, we hire the man','Criminals,Opportunity','My Life and Work',1931);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The way out of the depression is to start spending and doing things.','Depression and Prosperity','Detroit Times',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Depressions arent acts of God; like wars, they are the work of a small group of men who profit by them.','Depression and Prosperity,Wars','New Orleans Times Picayune',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Mr. Edison was comfortably well off-he was not a money maker.','Thomas Edison','Detroit News',1931);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Without doubt, Thomas Edison is my greatest contemporary.','Thomas Edison','N.Y American',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Edison, to a greater extent than has ever been recognized, is the father of American industrial methods.','Thomas Edison','N.Y American',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Although Mr. Edison was called The Wizard of the electrical world and everyone thought that electricity was the coming thing, he actually encouraged me to go with my second car.','Thomas Edison','True Story magazine',1935);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','What is life but education, anyway?','Education,Life','Detroit Times',1943);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','I believe in 100% Theory and 100% Practice. Theory without practical application is futile.','Education,Practice','N.Y American',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','A mans college and university degrees mean nothing to me until I see what he is able to do with them.','Education','New Orleans Times Picayune',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Teach children not to be gullible.','Education,Children','American Magazine',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','A nation that knows how to work will never suffer.','Labor,Work','Saturday Evening Post',1936);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','In teaching the children at Greenfield Village, we are trying to get back some of the solid McGuffey qualities.','Education,Greenfield Village,McGuffey','American Magazine',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Greatest thing in life is experience. Even mistakes have value.','Experience,Failure,Life','American Magazine',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','..That is what we are put in the world for, to get experience and to help others get it. It is the one thing no one can take away from us.','Experience','New York Times Magazine',1938);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Faith is one of the most effective tools in the human equipment. I believe that faith works.','Faith','American Magazine',1941);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The greatest day of my life was the day I married Mrs. Ford.','Clara Bryant Ford,Wife','N.Y Times Magazine',1938);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','I attribute whatever I may have been able to accomplish in life far more to my wife than to anything else and to everything else put together. But I cannot flatter myself that I found her because I was a good picker, I believe profoundly that we are guided, led, in such momentous matters.','Clara Bryant Ford,Marriage,Success,Wife','Forbes Magazine',1940);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','There can be no bosses in our country except the people. The job of the government is to serve, not to dominate.','Government','Detroit Times',1944);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','If governments would only understand that if people are left alone theyll work out their own salvation.','Government,Future','The Passing Show',1935);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Most of the sickness in the world is caused by eating too much.','Health,Diet','N.Y Times Magazine',1943);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Every one knows that insufficient rest and gorging are not good for anyone, either physically or mentally.','Health,Diet','N.Y Times Magazine',1938);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The time is coming when man will be able to determine the length of his lifespan by controlling his diet.','Health,Diet','Detroit News',1944);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','History doesnt mean dates and wars and textbooks to me; it means the unconquerable pioneer spirit of man.','History is Bunk','New Orleans Times Picayune',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','When I went to our American history books to learn how our forefathers harrowed the land, I discovered that the historians knew nothing about harrows. Yet our country has depended more on harrows than on guns or speeches. I thought that a history which excluded harrows, and all the rest of daily life, was bunk. And I think so yet.','History is Bunk','American Legion Magazine',1932);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','President Hoover has done everything any one could do to bring about improvement in business and industry. Everything President Hoover has advised or tried to put into effect has been sound.','Herbert Hoover, Depression','Washington Evening Star',1930);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The unhappiest man on earth is the one who has nothing to do.','Idleness,Happiness','Detroit Free Press',1944);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Idleness is the reason for many of our troubles.','Idleness','Detroit Times',1944);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','A monopoly of jobs in this country is just as bad as a monopoly of bread!','Labor Unions,Monopoly','Ford Gives Viewpoint on Labor',1937);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','This group (the union organizers) is asking us to sit still while it sells our men the jobs that have always been free.','Labor Unions;','Ford Gives Viewpoint on Labor',1937);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The great need of the world has always been for leaders. With more leaders we could have more industry. More industry, more employment and comfort for all.','Leadership,Industry','Barrons',1931);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Life, as I see it, is not a location, but a journey. Life flows.','Life','My Life and Work',1931);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Machines were devised not to do a man out of a job, but to take the heavy labor from mans back and place it on the broad back of the machine.','Machinery','Detroit Free Press',1930);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Machinery was invented by labor for labor-serving purposes. The wheel is the basis of the machine.','Machinery,The wheel','The Rotarian',1936);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Four women have helped me: mother, sister, mother-in-law and wife.','Family,Success,Women,Mother,Wife','True Story',1935);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Music and song are, in my opinion, so fine and necessary a part of life that without them we cannot be said really to live at all.','Music, Song','Detroit Public Schools, Dept. of Music Education Bulletin',1937);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Poetry without music may be beautiful, but music gives poetry wings and elevates it into song. That may be the reason for our love of song-it has wings and lifts us; with proper songs, it is a nourishing spiritual exercise.','Song, Music, Poetry','Detroit Public Schools, Dept. of Music Education Bulletin',1937);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Life is neither old or new, ancient or modern, but simply more or less vivid-any song or musical composition will live that expresses or reproduces this vividness of life.-From this you will see that I believe that music fills a great place. The teaching of it goes far to restore the balance and richness of life, and-I might add- the unit of life also.','Music, Song, Dance, Education','Detroit Public Schools, Dept. of Music Education Bulletin',1937);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','I havent put a pencil to a piece of paper, working out a problem, in years; I do it in my head.','Paper Work, Problem Solving','New Orleans Times Picayune',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Every man is entitled to make a darn fool of himself at least once in a lifetime. -Regarding Great War Peace Ship','Peace Ship, Great War, Life','B.C Forbes column',1942);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Public officials are all right if they stay in their proper sphere and perform their proper functions but when they get greedy for wider scope and more power and money they lose their value and become parasites.','Politicians, Politics, Public Officials','Detroit Times',1943);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','People didnt want war..we were forced in it..how fast we finish it depends on how free a hand our generals and admirals have. The less interference they get from the politicians the quicker theyll end it.','Politicians, War, World War II','Detroit Times',1943);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','I wouldnt have the Presidency or any political office-dont want anything to do with it nor have politics have anything to do with me.','Politics, Presidency','Detroit Times',1935);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','When prices go up, business goes down.','Prices, Business','Wall Street Journal',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','You cant tell me you can make any system or country work with low wages and high prices, and high wages with high prices dont mean anything when the prices eat up the wages and dont leave anything over.','Prices, Wages','Detroit Times',1938);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Profits are not financial-theyre social. Everybody profits from industry. Politicians dont understand profits because they can pay bills out of taxation.','Profits,Industry,Politicians','Wall Street Journal',1936);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Three most deleterious things of modern life in their present order of importance are: tobacco, alcohol and intemperate eating. Both alcohol and tobacco are taboo in plants.','Prohibition,Tobacco','New York American',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','I adopted the theory of reincarnation when I was 26. I got the idea from a book by Orlando Smith. Until I discovered this theory I was unsettled and dissatisfied-without a compass, so to speak. When I discovered reincarnation it was as if I had found a universal plan. I realized that there was a chance to work out my ideas. Time was no longer limited. I was no longer a slave to the hands of the clock. There was time enough to plan and to create. I wouldnt give five cents for seeing all the world, because I feel there is nothing in the five continents and on the five seas that I have not somehow seen. Somewhere is a master mind sending brain wave messages to us. There is a Great Spirit. I never did anything by my own volition. I was pushed by invisible forces within and without me. We inherit a native knowledge from a previous existence. Gospel of reincarnation is essence of all knowledge. I do not know where we come from or go to but we accumulate experience. Someday it will be possible to measure the soul. We all retain memories of past lives.','Reincarnation,Experience,Time','Detroit Times',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','(Instinct is) Probably the essence of past experience and knowledge stored up for later use. There are many, you know, who think that this life journey through the world is not the first one we have made. Havent you ever come across children who knew things that it was impossible for them to have learned? Have you ever gone to a place for the first time and felt sure that you had been there before? Thats one of the reasons I do not travel much.','Reincarnation,Children,Youth','New York Times Magazine',1938);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','If we could get all religions together on a common purpose-the elimination of jealousies and the things that make men covet anothers belongings, we would be a long way toward the goal of outmoding war, depression and poverty.','Religion,Depression,War,Poverty','Detroit Free Press',1944);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','In the Ford Motor Company we emphasize service equally with sales.','Customer Service,Ford Motor Company','Ford Service Manual',1918);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','A manufacturer is not through with his customer when a sale is completed. He has then only started with his customer. In the case of an automobile the sale of the machine is only something in the nature of an introduction. If the machine does not give service, then it is better for the manufacturer if he never had the introduction, for he will have the worst of all advertisements-a dissatisfied customer.','Customer Service','My Life and Work',1931);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','From the start I had my own ideas about how the business should run. I wanted it to benefit everybody who contributed to its success-stockholders, labor and the American public.','Stockholders,Ford Motor Company','Forbes Magazine',1941);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','A big business never becomes big by being a narrow society looking after only the interests of its organization and stockholders.','Stockholders,Business','Moving Forward',1933);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Stock market never made business-business makes the stock market.','Business,Stockholders,Stock Market','Detroit Free Press',1933);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Stock in the Ford Motor Company would increase the cost of the car. I am only interested in reducing the price of our car.','Stockholders,Stock,Ford Motor Company,Prices','Detroit Times',1935);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','I believe that any stock that is sold should have real value as automobile or bushel of potatoes, and stock market should be run as a vegetable market.','Stockholders','Hartford Courant',1935);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','No American ought to be compelled to strike for his rights. He ought to receive them naturally, easily, as a matter of course.','Strikes,Rights','Dearborn Independent',1919);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Anything that is not right, whether it temporarily favors the employees or the employers, cannot last-because it is not right.','Strikes,Rights','Dearborn Independent',1920);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Trees are among the most useful things grown.','Trees','Detroit News',1940);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Paying good wages is not charity at all-it is the best kind of business.','Wages,Business','Dearborn Independent',1919);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','If the boss stands in the way of men getting what they earn, he is not fit to be boss.','Wages,Business','Dearborn Independent',1919);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','A low wage business is always insecure.','Business,Wages','My Life and Work',1931);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Cutting wages is not the way to recovery. Raise wages and improve the product.','Wages,Depression','Chicago Tribune',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','No one ever wins a war.','War','Detroit News and Times',1942);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Wars are necessary to teach us lessons we seem unable to learn any other way.','War','New York Herald-Tribune',1941);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Money will ruin the life of any man who treats it like anything but a tool with which to work.','Wealth,Money','New Orleans Times Picayune',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','I dont expect to retire. Every man must work, thats his natural destiny.','Work,Retirement','N.Y World-Telegram',1933);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Only one thing makes prosperity, and that is work.','Work,Prosperity','Detroit Free Press',1931);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The basis of peace should be a world federation.','World Federation,Peace','New York World Telegram',1943);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Worry is the most wasteful thing in the world.','Worry','American Magazine',1936);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','No one can be helped unless he can be put in the way of helping himself.','Charity,Opportunity','New York American',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','People will try to fix world but world will fix people.','Depression,Prosperity World','Detroit News',1933);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Efficient industry is the sole key to prosperity','Industry,Prosperity','American Magazine',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Education not just preparation for life, but part if life itself-a continuous art.','Education,Life','Good Housekeeping',1934);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Anyone who does anything useful will not go unpaid.','Experience','New York Times Magazine',1938);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Mark my word: A combination airplane and motor car is coming..','Invention,Modernization','Forbes Magazine',1940);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Should a man quit at 40 he is failure-Retire at that age is sorry failure.','Retirement','William S Dutton',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','There should be no unemployment. There is large percentage of labor now which cannot make a living because wages are not high enough. That is industrys 2nd job. 1st job is to make good product. 2nd pay a good wage.','Unemployment,Wages,Youth,Education','Detroit Times',1936);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Most fashionable commodity in US is going to be old-fashioned common sense & work.','Work,Common Sense,Labor','Detroit Free Press',1933);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','..the home of tomorrow will make women free for work..free to work as they like, not as they are bound to do by the past..work is the only real happiness..industry itself has been modernized so that almost any job in industry may be taken over by a woman.','Women,Work,Labor','Toronto Star',1943);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','There can be no lasting peace where hatred exists. Hatreds will continue to arise as long as the causes of war are not rooted out and exposed.','War,Peace,Hatred','Detroit News',1944);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','(On collecting): I have been at it ten years. I collect them so that they will not be lost to America..We have no Egyptian mummies here, nor any relics of the Battle of Waterloo..nor any curios from Pompeii. It is strictly American..','Collecting','Detroit Times',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','[At Edison Institute] We shall reproduce the life of the country in its every age.','Collecting','Ford: Expansion and Challenge',1933);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The farther you look back, the farther you can look ahead.','The Past','Henry Ford and Greenfield Village',1938);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','When you once get an idea in which you believe with all your heart, work it out.','Ideas','Detroit Times',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','We want to reproduce all those instruments which were prepared and used in America once upon a time.','Collecting','American Russian Falcon',1932);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','When we are through, we shall have reproduced American life as lived; and that, I think, is the best way of preserving at least a part of our history and tradition.','Learning,Education,America,Tradition','Henry Ford and Greenfield Village',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','We ought to know more about the families who founded this nation, and how they lived. One way to do this is to reconstruct as nearly as possible the conditions under which they lived..','Learning,Education,America, Tradition','The American Historical Review',1931);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','I dont read history. Thats in the past. Im thinking of the future.','History,The Past,The Future','Americas Don Quixote',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Work is our sanity, our self-respect, our salvation. The days work is the center of everything.','Work','New York Times',1915);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','We now know that anything which is economically right is also morally right. There can be no conflict between good economics and good morals.','Morality, Economics','Moving Forward',1925);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','I dont like to read books. They muss up my mind.','Books,Reading','The New Henry Ford',1932);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','I wouldnt give five cents for all the art in the world.','Art','Detroit the Dynamic - Street',1921);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Thats the way to study history-by noting evolutionary processes.','History,Evolution','Barrons',1920);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','If you find out what men want and give them that, you are pleasing them. If you find out what is good for them and give them that, you are performing a service. Thats what we are trying to do.','Charity,Self-Help','Everybodys Magazine',1914);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','No one will ever get anywhere in this world unless he becomes a teacher, one who can show others how to do things.','Education,Teaching','New York Times',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','This is the only reason Greenfield Village exists-to give us a sense of unity with our people through the generations, and to convey the inspiration of American genius to our young men. As a nation we have not depended so much on rare or occasional genius as on the general resourcefulness of our people. That is our true genius, and I am hoping that Greenfield Village will serve that.','Greenfield Village,Edison Institute,America,Growth,Education','American Legion Monthly',1932);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','We want to have something of everything-we have types of every sort of wagon and carriage ever used in this country, from the covered wagon of the pioneer to the last style of buggy. We have nearly every type of agricultural instrument, every type of musical instrument, we have all kinds and sorts of furniture and household effects. One of these days the collection will have its own museum at Dearborn, and there we shall reproduce the life of the country in its every age.','Edison Institute,America','On Edison',1919);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Every business is a monarchy with, not a man, but an idea as king.','Business,Ideas','Electrical World',1929);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','When we are through, we shall have reproduced American life as lived; and that, I think is the best way of preserving at least a part of our history and tradition.','America,History,Tradition,Greenfield Village','Henry Ford and Greenfield Village',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Improvements have been coming so quickly that the past is being lost to the rising generation, and it can be preserved only by putting it in a form where it may be seen and felt. That is the reason behind this collection.','Edison Institute,Preservation of the Past,Greenfield Village','The American Historical Review',1931);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','We have enough in our country to let us deep into the springs of human life if we only cherished what we have.','America,Edison Institute,Greenfield Village','Detroit Times',1928);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','If you go into a union, they have got you, but what have you got?','Unions','Detroit News',1937);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The best way to make money in business is not to think too much about making it.','Money,Profit','The Wild Wheel',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','We have only started with the development of our country-we have not as yet, with all our talk of wonderful progress, done more than scratch the surface.','Development,Progress','My Life and Work',1922);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Any man can learn anything he will, but no man can teach except to those who want to learn. Education is preeminently a matter of quality, not amount','Education,Teaching','Ford News',1924);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Mass production is craftsmanship with the drudgery taken out of it.','Production','Ford News',1937);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','In the long run people are going to buy the cheapest and the best article no matter where it is made.','Business','Ford News',1937);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Burdening people with debt is an old deal not a new deal.','Debt','Ford News',1937);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The South has a future which it can shape for itself, and avoid the mistakes which the more populous parts of the country have made.','America,South','Ford News',1937);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','The best way is always the simplest. The attics of the world are cluttered up with complicated failures.','Simplicity','Ford News',1937);
INSERT INTO ford (author,quote,topic,source,year) VALUES ('Henry Ford','Money will ruin the life of any man who treats it like anything but a tool with which to work.','Money','Ford News',1937);